descp2: whether to perform partial pivoting. `True` by default. Partial pivoting makes the procedure more stable, but slower. Partial pivoting is unnecessary in some cases, including diagonally dominant and symmetric positive definite matrices (see e.g. theorem 9.12 in [1]).
